                       Access specifier or Visibility mode
                                                                               <<18-02026>>

ther are 3 types of Access specifier

1) public
2) private
3) protected

-> in structure by default all members are public but in class by default all members are private so we have to define in public mode.

1) public:
-> we can access class properties from anywher inside the class and outside the class

-> anywhere from the programe

2) private:
-> private means private data-even child class can't use private class data member and member function

-> so, private provide data protection and data hiding in cass functionality

-> only own class can access

3) protected:
->protected is a similar like private but protected member can access by own class child class

-> own class and child class.

